C. SDEM
The SDEM is used to enhance the spatial details of the feature maps that pass through the CSFM module, ensuring better spatial representation. As shown in Fig. 1 (c), the process also starts by concatenating R-D and then using a series of convolutional and attention mechanisms to enhance the spatial features. Multi-scale processing is conventionally implemented using a pyramid structure , a strategy we also adopt. The compressed feature maps are processed through multiple parallel atrous convolutions (ASPP). These features are then concatenated, followed by compression through an enhance MLP, denoted as φ3. A sigmoid activation function is applied to compute the attention weights, ultimately resulting in the attentionweighted feature map. Those operations are given by: Tc = ASPP([R, D])
