D. Deep Supervision
To further enhance the fusion at different levels, a method similar to depth supervision has been added on top of this model. The loss function for deep supervision is a weighted combination of losses at different scales, with 80% assigned to the loss of the final output and 20% assigned to the sum of losses from four intermediate outputs. In this approach, multiple intermediate outputi (corresponding to different scales) are compared to their respective ground-truth labels targeti, in addition to the final output which is also compared to the true target. This can be written as:
