E. Class Imbalance
The two datasets both share a common drawback: potential inhomogeneity in semantic annotation classes. To alleviate this issue, the following changes were made: From the data perspective, we applied common augmentation techniques to expand the dataset. From the evaluation metrics perspective, in addition to OA [14] , we introduced Macro F1 and Kappa [15] , allowing for a more comprehensive and accurate assessment. From the loss function perspective, the model is ultimately trained using a combination of weighted cross-entropy loss, Dice loss, and Focal loss.
