III. EXPERIMENT
A. Experimental implements
Experiments were conducted using PyTorch on a single RTX 3080 GPU with 30GB of memory. The model is trained using the AdamW optimizer, with a learning rate of 0.001 for the decoder layers and 0.0005 for the encoder layers. A cosine annealing scheduler is applied, and training is conducted with a batch size of 32. To mitigate overfitting, weight decay is set to 0.0005. The channel split ratio in the CSFM is 4, while the kernel size and number in the SDEM are 3 and 2 convolution layers. The model was validated on Potsdam and Vaihingen. Patches are extracted with a window size of 256. In Potsdam, a stride of 64 pixels is used, while in the Vaihingen, a stride of 32 pixels is applied. The stride of the window determines the overlap between adjacent patches, allowing them to be directly input into the overlap patch embedding layer.
