C. Model Complexity Analysis
We conducted a comprehensive complexity analysis of MDFformer (TABLE 3), benchmarking it against representative methods in the field. The results demonstrate that MDFformer achieves a favorable balance between computational efficiency and segmentation accuracy. MDFformer achieves 47.33G FLOPs, striking a balance between U-Net and CMFNet, and has 35.82M parameters to outperform U-Net (62.85M) and V1 (61.51M). These advantages stem from its lightweight design (leveraging weight connections, channel shuffle, and deep supervision) and efficient Adaptive Frequency Kernel for linear complexity, which together enable effective multi-scale feature extraction without excessive resource consumption.
